<section xml:id="Cryosphere_Epigraph">
  <title>Epigraph</title>
  <p>
    We were now revelling (sic) in the indescribable freshness of the Antarctic that seems to permeate one's being,
    and which must be responsible for that longing to go again which assails each returned explorer from polar regions.
    Sir Ernest Henry Shackleton, <em>The Heart of the Antarctic</em>, 1914, pg. 44
  </p>
